metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #5793
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: Lucky Oracles #55
metadata.description:
"Lucky Oracles" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022

Eko33, is a Swiss-French generative artist who has been at the forefront of digital arts since 1999 when he started writing code to create generative artworks and installations. He made his debut using a Commodore SX-64 and floppy disks. Since then, his work has been exhibited in Museums, International art fairs, and biennales. His work is focused on nonfigurative, generative art while using custom algorithms and innovative technology.

Official Website: https://www.eko33.com/ Official Twitter account: https://twitter.com/eko3316 Official Instagram account: https://www.instagram.com/eko33studio/ https://linktr.ee/eko33 "I create deterministic generative art based on crypto hash seeds. Maximizing algorithmic diversity."

If you want to receive an e-mail alert when I release new artwork subscribe here => https://eko33.com/email-alerts

metadata.name: Sixty# #156
metadata.description:
This idea was born from recent discussion on generative art and the path the medium is finding for itself. The project aims to take aesthetic concepts from sci fi graphic novels and blend them with generative systems of abstraction. 

The debate is between using previously established art forms to influence this new medium, or using a new medium to meticulously reproduce a previous medium. I believe there‚Äôs room to explore the full spectrum, and I am attempting to find the midpoint that fits my work and brings me the most happiness.

The title describes the eventual aesthetic objective, which is to create a piece which might look like a splash page a colorist alone has been given the freedom to design and explore their own specialty. It explores centralized polar compositions, vibrant colors, plus lots and lots of movement. 60# paper is a standard weight for printing of comic books and graphic novels.

Press ‚Äôs‚Äô in live view to save a .png

Created with p5.js and chroma.js

metadata.name: Daydreamer #51
metadata.description:
‚ÄòFor the artist communication with nature remains the most essential condition. The artist is human, himself nature; part of nature within natural space.‚Äô (Paul Klee, 1944) 


Working on long-form nature has an interesting side effect. On the one hand, you're attempting a shallow imitation of a landscape.... You are working with cold logic and code, vainly trying to control randomness to create this virtual facsimile, something you know is artificial.... 

....and yet.... even with all this left-brain activity, your right-brain pushes back, and imagines being there. While working on this project I found myself continually daydreaming, wandering off to hear the sounds of waterfalls, or the crunch of walking along a sandy lake shore. If you've ever wondered about coding, I urge you to learn. Daydreams await....


Press '1' once rendering is finished, to redraw at 5120x5120 resolution 
Press '2' to export without post-processing effects 

3rd party libraries (license text and links included in source) 
- p5.js - Creative coding framework 
- JS Topology Suite "JSTS", a port of Java Topology Suite "JTS" - High-level Geometry library 
- WebGLImageFilter, Dominic Szablewski - phoboslab.org 

I have tried to use soft blurs and shadows to give a sense of layering and depth to the scene. After viewing for a while, it reminds me of 3D paper-art. There are traits for colour and amount of birds, waterfalls, etc. but none are especially rare ‚Äì These properties are intended for filtering the collection.

metadata.name: Citta #27
metadata.description:
Citta as mind Citta as city. 

Citta is city of interconnected minds from future of Metropolis IX(Project id:13292), after singularity people uploaded their consciousness into inorganic self-constructing structures. 

There are 13 different mind-hives named with upper case letters, only "MC-00001" is monochrome rest is in color. "SCMB" and "SCCB' are in spiral formation due to their nature.

Press 1 to 8 export PNG 1000px to 8000px 
9 exports 10000px PNG 

Exports are dependent on CPU, so larger export might take time. Please be patient. If you cannot export reach me out.

Works best in Chrome browser. 

Created with p5.js and canvas api.
Murat Atimtay 2022 | @atimtay | www.muratatimtay.com

metadata.name: Gears ‚öô #168
metadata.description:
Gears are fascinating because they are one of the most basic and essential components of so many machines. They are simple yet elegant in their design and function, and they have been used for centuries to power all sorts of machines. 

This piece explores gears in an abstract way, chaining them with different rules - some more realistic than others - creating a variety of different settings.


Controls:
Mousewheel - Zoom in/out
Up/down Arrows - Increase/decrease gear speeds (hold left shift for coarse-tune, left ctrl for fine-tune)
Space - Pause
S - Download image
H - Hide gears
I - Invert gear render order
R - Reverse gear direction
F - Show/hide frame
V - Open plotter export menu
C - Show/hide connectors
T - Enable transparency on grab
D + Click - Hide gear
U - Unhide all gears

Plotter export options:
Default -  The background of your iteration will be exported into the SVG. Only possible for the styles "Brushed Straight", "Cables", and "Gears". 
None - No background
Lines - Parallel lines. Controlled by angle and spacing option
Circles - Concentric circles originating from the middle. Controlled by spacing.
Bg line spacing - spacing of the background lines
Bg line angle - angle of background lines (Only for "Background: Lines")
Min line length - Lines below this length will be discarded


Url parameter options:
lowPerf=1 - disables shadows
noMove=1 - start paused
multGears=X - Not enough gears in your iteration? Substitute X with any number to roughly multiply the amount of gears in your iteration. Use at your own risk ;-)
connectorShade=X - Shadeline spacing on connectors
spokesShade=X - Shadeline spacing on spokes
gearInnerShade - Shadeline spacing on inner gear rings
gearOuterShade - Shadeline spacing on outer gear rings
gearTeethringShade - Shadeline spacing on gear teeth rings


Best viewed on a desktop in Chrome. Requires a decent computer to run smoothly.
Supports touch controls and mobile, however it runs very slowly on firefox mobile.


2% chance to get a golden favicon, which will guarantee a reserve spot for all future mechanical drops.


Created in Vanilla.js

Libraries used: 
noise.js by Joseph Gentle

metadata.name: Sap song. Part II #60
metadata.description:
This artwork corresponds to the 2nd part of the ‚ÄòSap song‚Äô series. It seeks to expand the concept from new visual and sound variants.

Audiovisual generative artwork that continues with the proposal of excessive flows of organic forms. In time, frenetic arpeggios and populations of colorful plants with spiral flowers are emerging, all organized in their own way. And the sap again sings, feeds and shows us a constructive desire for afforestation.

The work has 3 moments:
I. ‚ÄúEnredo coral‚Äù
II. ‚ÄúRecitativo libre‚Äù
III. ‚ÄúCoda hacia la ra√≠z‚Äù

Original samplers of cello pizzicatos, marimba, music box, piano, and multiphonics of clarinet and flute.

[ s ] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)
[ f ] -> fullscreen

attributes.value: cello, marimba, music box and flute

metadata.description:
"All√©gories bool√©ennes" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at PARIS+ par Art Basel

This work is a continuation of research around the intersections of shapes that I have been exploring for a while. I wonder about the way in which they make it possible to bring out new compositions from superpositions of shapes that could initially represent a real disorder.

Controls:
‚Ä¢ "a": Play the animation
‚Ä¢ "s": Export the image (default 2160‚Ää√ó‚Ää3840px PNG)
‚Ä¢ "h": Change export settings to high resolution (then press "s" to export a 6480‚Ää√ó11520px PNG)
‚Ä¢ "m": Change export settings to medium resolution (then press "s" to export a 4320‚Ää√ó‚Ää7680px PNG)
‚Ä¢ "n": Back to 2160‚Ää√ó‚Ää3840px

Artwork by Julien Espagnon, 2022.

metadata.name: Broken Symmetries #1/3 #67
metadata.description:
"It was the best of times, it was the worst of times, it was the age of wisdom, it was the age of foolishness, it was the epoch of belief, it was the epoch of incredulity, it was the season of Light, it was the season of Darkness, it was the spring of hope, it was the winter of despair, we had everything before us, we had nothing before us..."
                                      Charles Dickens

This piece is the first in a planed series of three intended as studies on composition.

It is built entirely on thi.ng/umbrella libraries and template:

https://github.com/thi-ng/fxhash-tpl

Keyboard shortcuts

- 1 : render @ original resolution
- 2 : render @ 2 x resolution
- 4 : render @ 4 x resolution
- x : download canvas as PNG @ current resolution
- s : download canvas as SVG @ current resolution; This can be used with a plotter.
